cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DB

This paper deals with privacy-preserving policies and information leakage, which are topics commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The use of quantization operators and analysis of $k$-anonymity also suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of private datasets and worst-case quality constraints suggest a connection to database systems (cs.DB).
